---
description: Detailed responsibilities and constraints for each architecture layer (App, Features, Components, Lib). Apply when creating files inside app/, features/, components/, or lib/ to ensure each file respects its layer's boundaries.
globs: **/app/**/*.tsx,**/app/**/*.ts,**/features/**/*.tsx,**/features/**/*.ts,**/components/**/*.tsx,**/components/**/*.ts,**/lib/**/*.ts
alwaysApply: false
---

## Lib (`src/lib/`)

- Contains: utilities, hooks, services, types, constants
- Must be framework-agnostic when possible
- ❌ Must NOT import from `features/` or `components/`

## Components (`src/components/`)

- Contains only presentational (dumb) components
- Receives data and callbacks via props — no internal data fetching
- ❌ No business logic, no API calls, no global state access
- ✅ Must be pure and reusable across features

## Features (`src/features/<domain>/`)

- Contains all domain-specific logic: actions, queries, mutations, hooks, local components
- Can import from `lib/` and `components/`
- ❌ Must NOT import from other features
- ✅ Must expose its public API through `index.ts`

## App (`src/app/`)

- Next.js pages and layouts — entry points only
- Responsible for routing, providers, and composing features
- ❌ Must NOT contain business logic
- ❌ Must NOT be imported by any other layer
